The decision will not reflect in Indian-administered [Jammu and
Kashmir](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jammu_and_Kashmir) state as it has its
own constitution and criminal law, the [Ranbir Penal
Code,](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ranbir_Penal_Code) which still
criminalizes non-heterosexual sexual intercourse. Dr. Ajaz Ahmad Bund, a
social worker in Kashmir,
[told](https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/section-377-pride-not-
extended-to-
jk/articleshow/65714300.cms?utm_source=twitter.com&utm_medium=social&utm_campaign=TOIDesktop)
the Times of India:

> The Supreme Court judgment, I am hoping, will now initiate a debate and
> awareness about what it means to be gay or lesbian or transgender in
> Kashmir.

